# Iris Flower Prediction App

A Streamlit web application that predicts the type of Iris flower (Setosa, Versicolor, or Virginica) based on user-input parameters using a Random Forest Classifier.

## Features

- Interactive sliders for inputting flower measurements:
  - Sepal length (cm)
  - Sepal width (cm)
  - Petal length (cm)
  - Petal width (cm)
- Real-time prediction of Iris species
- Probability distribution across all possible species
- Clean, responsive UI with custom styling

## Technologies Used

- Python 3.x
- Streamlit (for web interface)
- Scikit-learn (for machine learning model)
- Pandas (for data handling)
- NumPy (for numerical operations)

## Installation

1. Clone this repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/okyerevansjohn/iris-flower-prediction.git
   cd iris-flower-prediction
   ```

2. Create and activate a virtual environment (recommended):
   ```bash
   python -m venv venv
   source venv/bin/activate  # On Windows use `venv\Scripts\activate`
   ```

3. Install the required packages:
   ```bash
   pip install -r requirements.txt
   ```

## Usage

1. Run the Streamlit app:
   ```bash
   streamlit run app.py
   ```

2. The app will open in your default web browser.

3. Adjust the sliders in the sidebar to input flower measurements.

4. View the predicted Iris species and prediction probabilities in the main window.

